{"id":"1101.4844","submitter":"Eimear Byrne","authors":"Eimear Byrne, Michael Kiermaier, Alison Sneyd","title":"Properties of Codes with Two Homogeneous Weights","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Finite Fields and Their Applications 18 (2012), 711-727","doi":"10.1016/j.ffa.2012.01.002","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO math.RA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Delsarte showed that for any projective linear code over a finite field of\ncharacteristic p with two nonzero Hamming weights w1 < w2 there exist positive\nintegers u and s such that w1 = (p^s)u and w2 = (p^s)(u+1). Moreover, he showed\nthat the additive group of such a code has a strongly regular Cayley graph.\nHere we show that for any proper regular projective linear code C over a finite\nFrobenius ring with two integral nonzero homogeneous weights w1 < w2, there is\na positive integer d, a divisor of the order of C, and positive integer u such\nthat w1 = du and w2 = d(u+1). In doing so, we give a new proof of the known\nresult that any proper regular projective two-weight code code yields a\nstrongly regular graph. We apply these results to existence questions on\ntwo-weight codes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jan 2011 15:20:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 2 Feb 2011 12:35:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2011 16:10:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 10 Mar 2011 17:28:30 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 8 Nov 2011 16:40:06 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 17 Jan 2012 22:56:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-16"}
